\begin{abstract}
\noindent {\sc Abstract:} Let $G$ be a real linear algebraic group and $L$ a finitely generated cosimplicial group. We prove that the space of homomorphisms ${\textnormal{Hom}}(L_n,G)$ has a homotopy stable decomposition for each $n\geq 1$. When $L_n=F_n/K_n$ where $F_n$ is the free group on $n$ generators, $K_n$ is a normal subgroup and $G$ is a compact Lie group, we show that the decomposition of ${\textnormal{Hom}}(F_n/K_n,G)$ is $G$-equivariant. 

The spaces ${\textnormal{Hom}}(L_n,G)$ assemble into a simplicial space ${\textnormal{Hom}}(L,G)$. When $G=U$ we show that its bar construction $B(L,U)$, has an $E_\infty$-ring space structure whenever ${\textnormal{Hom}}(L_0,U(m))$ is path connected for all $m\geq1$.
\end{abstract}

\section{Introduction}


The study of spaces of homomorphisms ${\textnormal{Hom}}(\Gamma,G)$, where $\Gamma$ is a finitely generated group and $G$ a compact Lie group, has been quite rich in its own, and has set the foundations of new cohomology theories called $q$-nilpotent topological K-theory (\cite{Ad3}). The building blocks of these theories are the spaces ${\textnormal{Hom}}(F_n/\Gamma^q_n,U)$, where $\Gamma^q_n$ is the $q$-th stage of the descending central series of $F_n$, the free group on $n$ letters, and $U={\underset{{m}}{\textnormal{colim}}\;}U(m)$. If we fix $q$ and let $n$ vary, these spaces form a simplicial space. Whenever a family $\{L_n\}_{n\geq0}$ of finitely generated groups fits into a cosimplicial group, it builds up a simplicial space ${\textnormal{Hom}}(L,G)$ induced by the spaces of homomorphisms ${\textnormal{Hom}}(L_n,G)$. We show that the families $\{F_n/\Gamma^q_n\}_{n\geq0}$, $\{F_n/F^{(q)}_n\}_{n\geq0}$ where $F^{(q)}_n$ is the $q$-th stage of the derived series of $F_n$, form a cosimplicial group, as well as the surface groups $\{T_n\}_{n\geq1}$.






